<section class="features syntax-notes">
    <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Feature</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">On Time, Every Time.<br class="desktop-br"> Note It.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-header">
                <span class="feature-number">01</span>
                <h3 class="feature-title">What You Write</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="feature-desc">Write your notes naturally on CueCard, or optionally add <code>[time]</code>
                and <code>[note]</code> tags to guide timing and tone.</p>
            <div class="notes-preview notes-preview-raw" aria-label="Sample of raw speaker notes">
                <div class="notes-content">
                    [time 00:15]
                    Imagine your notes floating above the deck. [note smile] I've
                    been using CueCard to do that.

                    [time 00:10]
                    It has a [note emphasize] timer and that sub-note
                    thingy, [note shrug a little] which makes me sound way more human.

                    [time 00:05]
                    [note widen the eyes] Dude, you gotta try this out.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-header">
                <span class="feature-number">02</span>
                <h3 class="feature-title">What You See</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="feature-desc">CueCard highlights timestamps, and action cues while the on-screen timer
                gently counts down.</p>
            <div class="notes-preview notes-preview-raw" aria-live="off">
                <div class="notes-content">
                    <span class="timestamp" data-time="15">[00:15]</span>
                    Imagine your notes floating above the deck. <span class="action-tag">[smile]</span> I've
                    been using CueCard to do that.

                    <span class="timestamp" data-time="75">[00:25]</span>
                    It has a <span class="action-tag">[emphasize]</span> timer and that sub-note thingy,
                    <span class="action-tag">[shrug a little]</span> which makes me sound way more human.

                    <span class="timestamp" data-time="105">[00:30]</span>
                    <span class="action-tag">[widen the eyes]</span> Dude, you gotta try this out.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
